define({"topics":[{"title":"MadCap Flare","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">MadCap Flare â€” a native XML content authoring application, which offers single-source         authoring in an environment that does not require to know any coding. <\/p>","href":"concept\/c_madcap_flare.html","attributes":{"data-id":"t_using_madcap_flare"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"t_using_madcap_flare-d340e235","topics":[]},{"title":"DITA and Oxygen","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The Darwin Information Typing Architecture (DITA) specification defines a set of         document types for authoring and organizing topic-oriented information, as well as a set of         mechanisms for combining, extending, and constraining document types. It is an open standard         that is defined and maintained by the OASIS DITA Technical Committee.<\/p>","href":"concept\/c_dita_and_oxygen.html","attributes":{"data-id":"t_applying_dita_and_oxygen"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"t_applying_dita_and_oxygen-d340e246","topics":[]},{"title":"Localization and memoQ","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Many people think that localization is mainly connected with translation. But         technical writing may be closely related to it as well. Localization, in this case, is the         adaptation of your documentation to the culture of the targeting country.<\/p>","href":"concept\/c_localization_and_memoq.html","attributes":{"data-id":"t_understanding_localization_and_memoq"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"t_understanding_localization_and_memoq-d340e257","topics":[]},{"title":"References","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">There are some additional resources that can be useful when you start your                 acquaintance with MadCap Flare; DITA and Oxygen; Localization and memoQ.<\/p>","href":"reference\/r_references6.html","attributes":{"data-id":"r_references6"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"r_references6-d340e268","topics":[]}]});